  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Building on prior work in self-refinement (Madaan et al., 2024), we leverage the demonstrated ability of LLMs to adjust outputs in diverse directions.",
    "The revision prompt, adapted from Wang et al. (2024e) and illustrated in Fig.",
    "2, refines an output based on four aspects: helpfulness, correctness, coherence, and verbosity.",
    "Given a token y t and a causal language model π eval for generating the rewards, we calculate the token-level reward by: r(x, y <t, y t) = σ log π eval (yt|x better,y<t) π eval (yt|xworse,y<t) -0.5, (3)",
    "where σ clips the reward value, and -0.5 clips recenters the original reward into range of [-0.5, 0.5]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Building on prior work in self-refinement (Madaan et al., 2024), we leverage the demonstrated ability of LLMs to adjust outputs in diverse directions."
  ]
}